  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 2 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 12 high, 2 medium, 25 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR); plus 9 other bases. 2 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is fog / freezing fog, mist and very low visibility  — most notably around London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR). Network hotspots: Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Tromsø Airport, Langnes (TOS/ENTC). Primary drivers: thunderstorm / convective risk, snow / blowing snow and low cloud base. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Shirak (LWN/UDSG), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and 9 others.",
